### Testing de API - ControlBook

## Usar con REST Client (VS Code)
Extensión: REST Client by Huachao Mao

---

### ✅ 1. LOGIN
POST http://localhost:3001/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "admin@controlbook.es",
  "password": "admin123"
}

# Guarda el token para usar en requests siguientes

---

### 📚 2. GET ALL CLASSES
GET http://localhost:3001/api/classes
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN_HERE

---

### ➕ 3. CREATE CLASS
POST http://localhost:3001/api/classes
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN_HERE

{
  "name": "Danza Street",
  "description": "Clase de danza urbana",
  "time": "10:00 - 12:00",
  "location": "Aula 5",
  "emoji": "🎭"
}

---

### 👥 4. GET STUDENTS
GET http://localhost:3001/api/students?classId=1
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN_HERE

---

### ➕ 5. CREATE STUDENT
POST http://localhost:3001/api/students
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN_HERE

{
  "name": "María García",
  "email": "maria@example.com",
  "team": "producción",
  "notes": "Muy participativa",
  "classId": 1
}

---

### ✅ 6. GET ATTENDANCE
GET http://localhost:3001/api/attendance?classId=1&date=2026-03-09
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN_HERE

---

### ✏️ 7. CREATE ATTENDANCE
POST http://localhost:3001/api/attendance
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN_HERE

{
  "studentId": 1,
  "classId": 1,
  "date": "2026-03-09",
  "time": "10:05",
  "status": "present",
  "notes": "Asistencia normal",
  "hasJustification": false,
  "justificationFile": null
}

### Status values: "present" | "absent" | "justified"

---

### 📊 8. GET REPORTS
GET http://localhost:3001/api/reports?classId=1&from=2026-01-01&to=2026-03-09
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN_HERE

---

### 📈 9. GET STATS
GET http://localhost:3001/api/stats
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN_HERE

---

### 🏥 10. HEALTH CHECK
GET http://localhost:3001/health

---

## 🔑 Obtener Token

1. Ejecuta el request de LOGIN
2. Copia el campo "token" de la respuesta
3. Reemplaza YOUR_TOKEN_HERE en los requests

Ejemplo:
```
Authorization: Bearer eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9...
```

---

## 💡 Tips

- Usa variables para simplificar:
  @token = <token_value>
  
- Los requests se pueden ejecutar uno por uno
- Verifica que el backend esté corriendo en :3001
- Todos los requests POST/PUT deben tener JWT

---

## 🔗 Base URL

Local: http://localhost:3001  
Production: https://controlbook-backend.up.railway.app

